external_knowledge:
- A batting average is calculated as the total number of hits divided by the total number of at-bats (which is represented by the total games in this context);
- "Top player" refers to the player with the highest batting average within their team;
- "More than 2 games played" ensures the player has a significant sample size for their batting average to be considered reliable.

- "Actors" refers to the players in the baseball context;
- "Stage" refers to the games played;
- "Roles" refers to the positions played by the players;
- "Affiliations" refers to the teams the players belong to;
- "Faced the various teams" means the players have played against different opponent teams.

- "Stars of the game" refers to top-performing players;
- "Hit the most home runs" refers to the highest number of home runs;
- "Boast the highest batting averages" refers to the best batting averages;
- "Belong to the highest-paying teams" refers to teams with the highest average salaries;
- "Play in the most-watched venues" refers to teams with the highest total attendance.

- "shining the brightest" refers to the player with the highest total home runs;
- "stellar batting average" refers to a high batting average, used to break ties in ranking;
- "star of the game" is a metaphor for the top-performing player.

- "shone the brightest" refers to players with a high number of games played and hits;
- "contribution to their team's batting prowess" is quantified by the player's hit percentage relative to the team's total hits;
- "under the sun and clouds" refers to games played under sunny and cloudy weather conditions.

- "star players" refers to the top 3 players in each team;
- "shining brightly" refers to having high batting average and on-base percentage;
- "league of baseball" refers to the context of the players and their teams.
